attacks.name: Growth Spurt
attacks.text: Take a Grass Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Powerful Bloom

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dive
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage for each of your Benched Lightning Pokémon.

attacks.text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Smokescreen
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokémon tries to use an attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

name: Old Amber
rules:
Play this card as if it were a 40-HP Basic Colorless Pokémon.
At any time during your turn, you may discard this card from play.
This card can't retreat.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Pokémon Flute
rules: Put a Basic Pokémon from your opponent's discard pile onto their Bench.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Mythical Slab
rules: Look at the top card of your deck. If that card is a Psychic Pokémon, put it into your hand. If it is not a Psychic Pokémon, put it on the bottom of your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Budding Expeditioner
rules: Put your Mew ex in the Active Spot into your hand.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Blue
rules: During your opponent's next turn, all of your Pokémon take −10 damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Leaf
rules: During this turn, the Retreat Cost of your Active Pokémon is 2 less.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
